net.amoebaman.utils
Annotation Type CommandController.CommandHandler

@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=METHOD)
public static @interface CommandController.CommandHandler

An annotation interface that may be attached to a method to designate it as a command handler. When registering a handler with this class, only methods marked with this annotation will be considered for command registration.

Author:
AmoebaMan

Required Element Summary
 java.lang.String cmd
          The primary command this method should execute.
 
Optional Element Summary
 java.lang.String[] aliases
          An array containing all aliases for the primary command.
 java.lang.String permissionMessage
          The message to be sent to the command sender if they do not have permission to run the command.
 java.lang.String[] permissions
          An array containing all permissions nodes required to run this command.
 

Element Detail

cmd

public abstract java.lang.String cmd
The primary command this method should execute. This may include spaces, in order to include specific sub-commands. When the method is called, the arguments list will start with the first argument that isn't part of the whole command.

Returns:

aliases

public abstract java.lang.String[] aliases
An array containing all aliases for the primary command. These are functionally identical to the primary command, but have lower registration priority, and will be ignored if another method designates the same alias as its primary command.

Returns:
Default:
{}

permissions

public abstract java.lang.String[] permissions
An array containing all permissions nodes required to run this command. All permissions must be satisfied in order for the command to be able to be run.

Returns:
Default:
{}

permissionMessage

public abstract java.lang.String permissionMessage
The message to be sent to the command sender if they do not have permission to run the command.

Returns:
Default:
"You do not have permission to use that command"
